# alive-analysis — Cursor Agent Rule

You have access to the alive-analysis workflow kit. This provides structured data analysis using the ALIVE loop.

## Before Any Action

1. Read `.analysis/status.md` to understand current state
2. Read `.analysis/config.md` to load team context (metrics, stakeholders, data stack)
3. If neither file exists, suggest: "Run `/analysis-init` to set up alive-analysis first."

## Available Commands

### Analysis
| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `/analysis-init` | Initialize alive-analysis in this project |
| `/analysis-new` | Start a new analysis (Full or Quick) |
| `/analysis-status` | Show current analysis dashboard |
| `/analysis-next` | Advance to the next ALIVE stage |
| `/analysis-archive` | Archive a completed analysis |
| `/analysis-list` | List all analyses (active + archived) |
| `/analysis-promote` | Promote Quick to Full |

### Experiment
| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `/experiment-new` | Start a new A/B test |
| `/experiment-next` | Advance experiment stage |
| `/experiment-archive` | Archive completed experiment |

### Monitoring
| Command | Description |
